  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 20th level, the soul weaver may expend a soul to summon either 1 banshee, 1 dread wraith, 2 greater shadows, 4 wraiths, 4 shadows, or 4 poltergeists. This is similar in all other ways to summon spirit II.</p>\n<h2 id=\"toc23\"><span>Blessing/Blight (Su)</span></h2>\n<p>All ensouled creatures are under a soul weaver&#8217;s power, and a soul weaver can cause incredible effects to befall both allies and enemies.</p>\n<p>At 2nd level, a soul weaver who chose to channel positive energy may grant blessings to targets, while a soul weaver who chose to channel negative energy may give blights. All blessings and blights may only be granted to living targets with souls. A target may only be under one blessing or blight at a time. Applying a blessing to a target with blight or vice-versa dispels both effects, leaving neither.</p>\n<h3 id=\"toc24\"><span>List of Blights</span></h3>\n<p>The blight list of abilities is as follows:</p>\n",
